Bovine tuberculosis, Belgium
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 7 Oct 2016 from Dr Jean-Fran√ßois Heymans, Director, Animal Health and Safety of Products of Animal Origin, Federal Agency for the Safety of the Food Chain (FASFC), Bruxelles, Belgium

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 8 Sep 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 28 Sep 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: November 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Mycobacterium bovis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Leuze-En-Hainaut, Hainaut
Date of start of the outbreak: 8 Sep 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 146 / 2 / 1 / - / 1
Affected population: Dairy cattle

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.37 / 0.68 / 50 / **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Epidemiological investigation is on-going.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: disinfection/disinfestations; traceability; stamping out; official destruction of animal products

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
Veterinary and Agrochemical Research Centre (CODA-CERVA) (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / pathogenic agent isolation on culture / 28 Sep 2016 / Positive
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 14 Sep 2016 / Positive
Cattle / real-time PCR / 14 Sep 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

